<title>Settings &amp; configuration</title>

<p>The <link xref="tech-gsettings">GSettings</link> GIO API can be used to read and write application settings. This can store a wide variety of data, such as integers and arrays of strings. GSettings transparently uses the GNOME settings database. User interface controls can be bound to settings with a single function, so that they automatically update.</p>

